class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gku1665702653234.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gku1665702653234.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gku1665702653234.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gku1665702653234\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      /svc\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Compile Uniface service components.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gku1665702653234__section_w2915ab1b5b1_w2916ab1b5_w2917ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__p_d151328e1_d151329e1_d151330e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/svc</span> {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/inf</span> | <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/war</span>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/cmi</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ilv</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">= </code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/lis</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sym</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>} {<code class=\"ph codeph\">/aft=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Datetime</var>} {<code class=\"ph codeph\">/bef=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Datetime</var>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/iap</span> | {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tpl</span>} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/plt</span>}} {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/nodebug</span>} {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Service</var>}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gku1665702653234__section_w2918ab1b5b3_w2919ab1b5_w2920ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d267659e133\">\n                  \n Sub-Switches\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e22\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ide1665702625805.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ide1665702625805.html\" title=\"Compile objects modified after and/or before the date specified.\">/aft= or /bef=</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e27\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkq1665702626173.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkq1665702626173.html\" title=\"Specifies whether compiled module information is generated when compiling objects with a command line switch.\">/cmi</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e32\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bhc1665702625956.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bhc1665702625956.html\" title=\"Compile all the specified development objects, regardless of their purpose (Normal, Palettes, and Templates).\">/iap</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e37\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hsx1665702626834.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hsx1665702626834.html\">/ilv</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e42\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"czj1665702653450.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/czj1665702653450.html\" title=\"Display the information listing plus warning and error messages when compiling.\">/inf</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e48\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"stn1665702655266.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/stn1665702655266.html\" title=\"Produce compile listings of ProcScript modules for components, application shells, menus, and global ProcScript.\">/lis</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e53\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrz1665702655781.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrz1665702655781.html\" title=\"Instruct Uniface to compile the application shell, component, or global ProcScript so that it cannot be debugged.\">/nodebug</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e58\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"twc1665702654010.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/twc1665702654010.html\" title=\"Compiles main development objects that are defined as palettes (Purpose = P), but does not generate runtime objects. Use it to ensure that palettes do not contain ProcScript syntax errors.\">/plt</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e63\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqo1665702655995.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqo1665702655995.html\" title=\"Specify whether object references are generated during compilation, and where they are located.\">/sym</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e68\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fmo1665702653737.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmo1665702653737.html\" title=\"Compiles main development objects that are defined as templates (Purpose = T), but does not generate runtime objects. Use it to ensure that templates do not contain ProcScript syntax errors.\">/tpl</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6233e73\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wmw1665702653597.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmw1665702653597.html\" title=\"Display warning and error messages when compiling.\">/war</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gku1665702653234__section_w2921ab1b5b5_w2922ab1b5_w2923ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d267659e262\">\n                  \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__p_d151337e1_d151338e1_d151339e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Service</var>—name of the service to compile; if omitted, all services are compiled (after considering any sub-switches). Use wildcard characters to specify multiple services.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gku1665702653234__section_w2924ab1b5b7_w2925ab1b5_w2926ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d267659e274\">\n                  \n Use With\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d5931e20\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.exe</span>—Uniface IDE</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gku1665702653234__section_w2927ab1b5b9_w2928ab1b5_w2929ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d267659e286\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6231e20\">By default, this switch compiles normal components (the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Purpose</span> property is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">N (Normal)</code>. To compile components that are defined as templates\n\t\tor palettes (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Purpose</span> is <code class=\"ph codeph\">T (Template)</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">P (Palette)</code>), you can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tpl</span> and\n\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/plt</span> sub-switches. If you want to compile the components regardless of their purpose, you can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/iap</span> (include all purposes) sub-switch.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6231e48\">When compiling from the command, only \t\terror messages are shown by default. (Compiling interactively displays both error and warning messages.) Use\n\t\tthe <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/inf</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/war</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/lis</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ilv</span> sub-switches to\n\t\tincrease the amount of information displayed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__d6231e63\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/nodebug</span> sub-switch to\n\t\tspecify that the compiled component(s) cannot be debugged.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gku1665702653234__section_w2930ab1b5c11_w2931ab1b5_w2932ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d267659e342\">Example: Using /svc </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__p_d151361e1_d151362e1_d151363e1\">Compile all services:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/svc *</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__p_d151364e1_d151365e1_d151366e1\">Compile all services with names ending with <code class=\"ph codeph\">VAL</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/svc *VAL</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__p_d151367e1_d151368e1_d151369e1\">Compile the service GENINFO and create a ProcScript module listing:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/svc /lis geninfo</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gku1665702653234__p_d151370e1_d151371e1_d151372e1\">Compile all services except GENINFO, displaying warning messages. Try double quotation marks (<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>) if your system does not allow the wildcard character exclamation point (!).</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/svc /war \"!geninfo\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgf1704692857485.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Services</a><p>Service components are designed to handle most Uniface application processing. They usually group together those entities that are needed to support the processing of a business object, such as an order or a customer. For example, an order update service could combine entities used to update both customer and order entities.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xfc1665702625593.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Compiling from the IDE Command Line</a><p>The IDE command line can be used to compile multiple objects without opening the IDE. It is especially useful for automating compilation by means of batch scripts.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527898\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527898\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/svc Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /svc Compile Uniface service components. /svc { /inf | /war } { /cmi = Value } { /ilv = Value } { /lis = Value } { /sym = Value } { /aft= Datetime } { /bef= Datetime } { /iap | { /tpl } { /plt }} { /nodebug } { Service } Sub-Switches /aft= or /bef= /cmi /iap /ilv /inf /lis /nodebug /plt /sym /tpl /war Parameters Service —name of the service to compile; if omitted, all services are compiled (after considering any sub-switches). Use wildcard characters to specify multiple services. Use With ide.exe —Uniface IDE Description By default, this switch compiles normal components (the Purpose property is set to N (Normal) . To compile components that are defined as templates or palettes ( Purpose is T (Template) or P (Palette) ), you can use the /tpl and /plt sub-switches. If you want to compile the components regardless of their purpose, you can use the /iap (include all purposes) sub-switch. When compiling from the command, only error messages are shown by default. (Compiling interactively displays both error and warning messages.) Use the /inf , /war , /lis and /ilv sub-switches to increase the amount of information displayed. Use the /nodebug sub-switch to specify that the compiled component(s) cannot be debugged. Example: Using /svc Compile all services: /svc * Copy Compile all services with names ending with VAL : /svc *VAL Copy Compile the service GENINFO and create a ProcScript module listing: /svc /lis geninfo Copy Compile all services except GENINFO, displaying warning messages. Try double quotation marks ( \" ) if your system does not allow the wildcard character exclamation point (!). /svc /war \"!geninfo\" Copy Related Links Services Service components are designed to handle most Uniface application processing. They usually group together those entities that are needed to support the processing of a business object, such as an order or a customer. For example, an order update service could combine entities used to update both customer and order entities. Compiling from the IDE Command Line The IDE command line can be used to compile multiple objects without opening the IDE. It is especially useful for automating compilation by means of batch scripts. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}